  "prompt": "What are the comparative legal approaches to money laundering across different nations?",
  "response": "Here's an overview of comparative legal approaches to money laundering across different jurisdictions:\n\n1. United States\n- Comprehensive Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA) as foundational legislation\n- Strict reporting requirements for financial institutions\n- Aggressive prosecution and substantial penalties\n\n2. European Union\n- Unified regulatory framework through Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- Emphasizes customer due diligence\n- Promotes information sharing between member states\n- Increasingly stringent requirements for financial transparency\n\n3. Switzerland\n- Historically known for banking secrecy\n- Gradually implementing more robust AML regulations\n- Strong emphasis on financial intermediary compliance\n- Significant penalties for non-compliance\n\n4. United Kingdom\n- Sophisticated legal framework\n- Proceeds of Crime Act as key legislation\n- Advanced financial intelligence capabilities\n- Focus on international cooperation\n\n5. Singapore\n- Strict regulatory environment\n- Comprehensive legal framework\n- Advanced technological monitoring systems\n- Severe penalties for non-compliance\n\n6. China\n- Centralized regulatory approach\n- Growing emphasis on international AML standards\n- Increasing cooperation with global financial institutions\n- Strict governmental oversight\n\n7. Russia\n- Developing AML legal infrastructure\n- Increasing regulatory complexity\n- Variable enforcement mechanisms\n- Ongoing international engagement\n\nThese approaches demonstrate varying levels of regulatory sophistication and enforcement strategies.",
